label.value: Sarcoma G2

value.value: A sarcoma with a total score of 4 or 5 according to the FNCLCC guidelines.

label.value: Ampulla of Vater Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of ampulla of Vater cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Endoscopic ultrasonography and computed tomography are effective in preoperative staging and in evaluating resectability of ampullary carcinomas. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ampulla of Vater Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of ampulla of Vater cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Ampulla of Vater Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ampulla of Vater cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ampulla of Vater Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ampulla of Vater cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumors (including carcinoid tumors) are now staged by a single pancreatic staging system. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ.  This also includes the PanIn III classification.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Sarcoma G3

value.value: A sarcoma with a total score of 6 or higher according to the FNCLCC guidelines.

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor limited to the pancreas, measuring 2 cm or less in greatest dimension.. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: PI3Ka/mTOR Inhibitor PKI-179

value.value: A second generation, small-molecule mimetic of ATP that targets the mammalian target of rapamycin (mTOR) with potential antineoplastic activity. PKI-179 selectively inhibits mTOR and phosphoinositide-3-kinase (PI3K) alpha. By inhibiting the PI3K/mTOR signaling pathway, this agent may inhibit tumor cell proliferation and survival.

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor limited to the pancreas, measuring more than 2 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor extending beyond the pancreas but without involvement of the celiac axis or the superior mesenteric artery. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor involving the celiac axis or the superior mesenteric artery (unresectable primary tumor). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer with no regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer with regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Triaziquone

value.value: An aziridinylbenzoquinone-based alkylating agent with potential antineoplastic activity. The alkylating group in triaziquone becomes activated upon reduction of quinone to the hydroquinone form. This eventually results in the alkylation and crosslinking of DNA, thereby inhibiting DNA replication followed by an induction of apoptosis. In addition, reactive oxygen species may form during redox cycling which may contribute to this agent's cytotoxic activity.

label.value: High Grade Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor

value.value: A malignant peripheral nerve sheath tumor that is high-grade.

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Information necessary for the clinical staging of pancreatic cancer can be obtained from physical examination and three dimensional radiographic imaging studies, which include triphasic, contrast-enhanced multislice computed tomography or magnetic resonance imaging (MRI). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine and Endocrine Pancreatic Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Exocrine or endocrine pancreatic cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: PLAC8 Gene

value.value: This gene may be involved in the regulation of dendritic cells.

label.value: PLAC8 wt Allele

value.value: Human PLAC8 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 4q21.22 and is approximately 24 kb in length. This allele, which encodes placenta-specific gene 8 protein, may play a role in the modulation of dendritic cell activity.  Aberrant expression of the gene may be involved in leukemia relapse.

label.value: Placenta-Specific Gene 8 Protein

value.value: Placenta-specific gene 8 protein (115 aa, ~13 kDa) is encoded by the human PLAC8 gene. This protein may be involved in dendritic cell activation.

label.value: FAM13A Gene

value.value: This gene may be involved in the regulation of GTPases.

label.value: FAM13A wt Allele

value.value: Human FAM13A wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 4q22.1 and is approximately 550 kb in length. This allele, which encodes protein FAM13A, may play a role in the modulation of GTP metabolism. Polymorphism may be associated with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease and aberrant expression may play a role in leukemia relapse.

label.value: Poorly Differentiated Angiosarcoma

value.value: An angiosarcoma characterized by the presence of significant cytologic atypia, necrosis and high mitotic activity.

label.value: Protein FAM13A

value.value: Protein FAM13A (697 aa, ~80 kDa) is encoded by the human FAM13A gene. This protein may be involved in the activation of GTPases.

label.value: PRKN Gene

value.value: This gene may play a role in the mediation of proteasomal targeting.

label.value: PRKN wt Allele

value.value: Human PRKN wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6q26 and is approximately 1380 kb in length. This allele, which encodes E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase parkin protein, may be involved in the modulation of ubiquitination. Mutation of the gene is associated with Parkinson disease. Somatic mutations may be associated with either ovarian or lung adenocarcinoma.

label.value: E3 Ubiquitin-Protein Ligase Parkin

value.value: E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase parkin (465 aa, ~52 kDa) is encoded by the human PRKN gene. This protein may play a role in the ubiquitination of proteins targeted for proteasomal degradation.

label.value: ADAM8 Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in the mediation of proteolysis.

label.value: ADAM8 wt Allele

value.value: Human ADAM8 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 10q26.3 and is approximately 14 kb in length. This allele, which encodes disintegrin and metalloproteinase domain-containing protein 8, plays a role in the regulation of proteolysis. The gene may be involved in neurodegeneration and allergic respiratory diseases.

label.value: Disintegrin and Metalloproteinase Domain-Containing Protein 8

value.value: Disintegrin and metalloproteinase domain-containing protein 8 (824 aa, ~89 kDa) is encoded by the human ADAM8 gene. This protein is involved in proteolysis.

label.value: DLL4 Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in the notch signal transduction pathway.

label.value: DLL4 wt Allele

value.value: Human DLL4 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 15q14 and is approximately 10 kb in length. This allele, which encodes Delta-like protein 4, plays a role in the modulation of notch signaling and may play a role in neovascularization.

label.value: Delta-Like Protein 4

value.value: Delta-like protein 4 (685 aa, ~75 kDa) is encoded by the human DLL4 gene. This protein is involved in the initiation of notch signaling.

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage I Adult Hodgkin Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage I: Involvement of a single lymph node region (I); or localized involvement of a single extralymphatic organ or site in the absence of any lymph node involvement (IE) (rare in Hodgkin lymphoma).

label.value: CTSK Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in osteoclastic bone resorption.

label.value: CTSK wt Allele

value.value: Human CTSK wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1q21 and is approximately 12 kb in length. This allele, which encodes cathepsin K protein, plays a role in the regulation of both proteolysis and osteoclastic bone resorption. Mutation of the gene is associated with pycnodysostosis.

label.value: Cathepsin K

value.value: Cathepsin K (329 aa, ~37 kDa) is encoded by the human CTSK gene. This protein is involved in proteolysis.

label.value: Type of Valve Dysfunction

value.value: A finding that indicates the specific type of abnormality that is present in a heart valve such as insufficiency, regurgitation or prolapse.
